TabletReader is an e-book reader for touch enabled devices.
Written into C++ and QML using Qt framework, tabletReader 
is targeted at Linux OSs, but Windows is also supported
(see https://github.com/cristeab/tabletReader).

Dependencies:
- Qt >= 4.7
- QtMobility >= 1.2
- qt-poppler
- chmlib
- djvulibre

Compilation and installation (Linux only):
- use qmake in the root folder, then make and make install

Notes:
- by default the application is compiled in release mode, with 
support for touch-enabled devices running Plasma notebook (KDE) on Linux 
(tested on openSUSE 12.1)
- for Plasma desktop (KDE) you might need to define DESKTOP_APP
in src/src.pro
